            "answer_text": "In questions like these, the first thing that you should try to do is to find out the total amount of work in terms of Man-Days or try and figure out efficiency on a unit basis.  In this question, we are given that 10 painters can paint 8 houses in 7 days.  => 10*7 Painter-days are required for painting 8 houses => 70/8 painter-days are required for each house.  We need to paint 13 houses, so total amount of work to be done = 13*70/8 painter-days. We have 6 painters available.  Time required = Work required / Resources available = (13*70/8) / 6 = 18.96 days So, it will take approximately 19 days to finish painting the houses.  ",
